    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-12T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="778"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760i.6111/58: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-12T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 12, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 12—10:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>733. My 653, September 29, 6 p.m.<note n="50" xml:id="d778fn50">Not
                        printed.</note> The Soviet press reports today that the protocol regarding
                    the disposition of Soviet land and air forces in Estonia was signed in
                        Tallinn<note n="51" xml:id="d778fn51">Beginning on October 18, 1939, Soviet
                        troops marched across Estonia in two columns, without incident, to their
                        destinations.</note> and that an agreement was reached with regard to naval
                    questions. The press likewise reports that General <persName corresp="#p_LJ1"
                        >Laidoner</persName>, Commander-in-Chief of the Estonian Army, has accepted
                    an invitation to visit Moscow.</p>
                <p>The departure of the Latvian trade delegation for Moscow is likewise reported in
                    a despatch from Riga.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Riga.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
